{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"nut milk bag, bowl, egg rings, non-stick frying pan, fine-mesh sieve, tongs, thermal serving bowl or plate, refrigerator, stove top","id":"r431908","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-S_-EBielZ2c\/XZWZ9nMu6dI\/AAAAAAAAeUI\/fIAi7sMSiwUgY8kGAUrwmCsYFkuk_RhowCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rCf4Bvv7U43K5jk9.png","title":"Orange grove beghrir with orange blossom yoghurt","publishedAt":"2019-04-04T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"500 g natural yoghurt"},{"content":"1 - 2 tbsp orange blossom water"},{"content":"1 tsp dried instant yeast"},{"content":"½ tsp sugar"},{"content":"300 g water"},{"content":"130 g fine semolina, plus extra for sprinkling"},{"content":"200 g plain flour"},{"content":"¼ tsp cream of tartar"},{"content":"1 tsp salt"},{"content":"200 g milk"},{"content":"1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda"},{"content":"butter, for frying"},{"content":"orange marmalade, to serve"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6.9 g","fat":"4.7 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"33.8 g","calories":"877.5 kJ \/ 208.9 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Line a fine-mesh sieve with a nut milk bag and place over a bowl.  Place bowl with sieve onto mixing bowl lid and weigh yoghurt into it. Add orange blossom water and place into refrigerator until mixture thickens (approx. 3 hours)."},{"content":"Place yeast, sugar and water into mixing bowl and heat <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add semolina, flour, cream of tartar, salt and milk and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Set mixture aside to prove in mixing bowl for 1 hour."},{"content":"Add bicarbonate of soda and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Leave mixture to prove in mixing bowl for a further 5 minutes or until it starts to bubble."},{"content":"Place a non-stick frying pan over medium heat and add butter. Grease 4 egg rings with butter and place into frying pan for 1 minute to warm. Sprinkle some semolina into each ring. Fill each ring three-quarters full with batter. Keep heat at medium and cook for 5 minutes or until surface is dry to the touch. Carefully remove rings with tongs, then flip beghrir over and cook for a further 3 minutes (adjust heat as needed to ensure cooking is slow and even). Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or onto a plate and cover to keep warm. Add more butter to pan, re-grease rings as needed and repeat process for remaining batter (makes approx. 10 beghrir). Serve with Orange blossom yoghurt and marmalade."}],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","4h 50m","10 pieces"]}